WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:24.390 align:middle line:90%


00:00:24.390 --> 00:00:27.270 align:middle line:10%
>> After stage four cancer
took Anita Moorjani down to 80

00:00:27.270 --> 00:00:31.450 align:middle line:10%
pounds, she slipped into a coma
and was given days to live.

00:00:31.450 --> 00:00:33.090 align:middle line:10%
And the only reason
Anita is here

00:00:33.090 --> 00:00:35.460 align:middle line:10%
today is because of her
choice to live her life

00:00:35.460 --> 00:00:38.730 align:middle line:10%
in a radically loving way.

00:00:38.730 --> 00:00:41.190 align:middle line:10%
Anita first wrote about her
transformational experience

00:00:41.190 --> 00:00:44.250 align:middle line:10%
in a blog and that's where
the late and amazing Wayne

00:00:44.250 --> 00:00:45.900 align:middle line:10%
Dyer found her story.

00:00:45.900 --> 00:00:50.100 align:middle line:10%
And encouraged her to write her
first book, "Dying to Be Me."

00:00:50.100 --> 00:00:54.180 align:middle line:10%
Her latest book is called
"Sensitive is the New Strong."

00:00:54.180 --> 00:00:56.520 align:middle line:84%
And it gives us tools
to so many of us

00:00:56.520 --> 00:00:59.070 align:middle line:84%
who are intuitive
beings to be able to be

00:00:59.070 --> 00:01:01.920 align:middle line:90%
strong in a fear based world.

00:01:01.920 --> 00:01:03.010 align:middle line:90%
I'm so glad you're here.

00:01:03.010 --> 00:01:04.239 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:01:04.239 --> 00:01:05.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Thank you for
inviting me, Lisa.

00:01:05.960 --> 00:01:08.060 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm so glad you're here
really like in general.

00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:11.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, I am so happy to
be here on this planet.

00:01:11.830 --> 00:01:16.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, yeah, tell me a little
bit about the story of when you

00:01:16.590 --> 00:01:22.560 align:middle line:84%
had experienced the epiphany
in the hospital that you were

00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:26.460 align:middle line:84%
living a according to
your cultural beliefs.

00:01:26.460 --> 00:01:27.630 align:middle line:90%
What was that?

00:01:27.630 --> 00:01:29.520 align:middle line:90%
>> So, well, the thing is--

00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:30.480 align:middle line:90%
so I was dying.

00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:32.370 align:middle line:90%
I had end stage cancer.

00:01:32.370 --> 00:01:33.760 align:middle line:10%
And I'd gone into a coma.

00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:36.810 align:middle line:10%
And the doctors had told
my family that this was it.

00:01:36.810 --> 00:01:39.150 align:middle line:10%
I wasn't coming back.

00:01:39.150 --> 00:01:41.190 align:middle line:10%
And I had tumors.

00:01:41.190 --> 00:01:42.330 align:middle line:90%
I had lymphoma.

00:01:42.330 --> 00:01:45.180 align:middle line:84%
Tumors-- some of them
the size of golf balls

00:01:45.180 --> 00:01:47.760 align:middle line:84%
all around my neck
and my breasts,

00:01:47.760 --> 00:01:50.910 align:middle line:84%
under my arms, and all
the way to my abdomen.

00:01:50.910 --> 00:01:53.160 align:middle line:84%
And my lungs were
filled with fluid.

00:01:53.160 --> 00:01:58.170 align:middle line:84%
And I weighed 85 pounds or 80
pounds, actually, at that time.

00:01:58.170 --> 00:02:02.220 align:middle line:84%
I was connected to an oxygen
tank, heart rate machine--

00:02:02.220 --> 00:02:04.560 align:middle line:84%
I was just-- had
all these tubes.

00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:05.640 align:middle line:10%
And I was gone.

00:02:05.640 --> 00:02:07.090 align:middle line:10%
I was like pretty much gone.

00:02:07.090 --> 00:02:11.190 align:middle line:10%
And the doctors told my
family that this was it.

00:02:11.190 --> 00:02:16.080 align:middle line:10%
But unbeknownst to all of
them I was actually aware

00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:19.290 align:middle line:10%
of everything that was
happening around my body.

00:02:19.290 --> 00:02:24.120 align:middle line:84%
It was like I was no
longer in my physical body.

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:28.680 align:middle line:84%
I could even see my body lying
there on the hospital bed.

00:02:28.680 --> 00:02:33.130 align:middle line:90%
And the thing is I felt amazing.

00:02:33.130 --> 00:02:34.980 align:middle line:90%
I felt powerful.

00:02:34.980 --> 00:02:36.630 align:middle line:90%
I felt free.

00:02:36.630 --> 00:02:40.020 align:middle line:84%
And all the pain and
discomfort from all these years

00:02:40.020 --> 00:02:41.190 align:middle line:90%
of the cancer--

00:02:41.190 --> 00:02:42.750 align:middle line:90%
that was all gone.

00:02:42.750 --> 00:02:44.420 align:middle line:90%
And the fear was gone.

00:02:44.420 --> 00:02:47.850 align:middle line:84%
Because I had a fear of
cancer, a fear of death,

00:02:47.850 --> 00:02:50.705 align:middle line:84%
and a fear of the
treatment for cancer.

00:02:50.705 --> 00:02:52.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Those were your
biggest fears?

00:02:52.080 --> 00:02:54.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Those were my biggest fears.

00:02:54.390 --> 00:02:56.310 align:middle line:90%
And here I was--

00:02:56.310 --> 00:02:58.080 align:middle line:90%
I was aware I was dying.

00:02:58.080 --> 00:03:00.450 align:middle line:90%
And it was all gone.

00:03:00.450 --> 00:03:01.740 align:middle line:90%
The fears were gone.

00:03:01.740 --> 00:03:04.890 align:middle line:84%
So it just felt
really, really amazing.

00:03:04.890 --> 00:03:09.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Isn't it incredible how we
create our greatest fear if we

00:03:09.360 --> 00:03:10.590 align:middle line:90%
focus on them?

00:03:10.590 --> 00:03:13.450 align:middle line:84%
And you had-- you had
focus a lot on those

00:03:13.450 --> 00:03:14.250 align:middle line:90%
in a different way.

00:03:14.250 --> 00:03:15.810 align:middle line:90%
You did things different, right?

00:03:15.810 --> 00:03:17.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, I did things
very different.

00:03:17.760 --> 00:03:21.570 align:middle line:84%
So I grew up living
a fear-based life.

00:03:21.570 --> 00:03:24.960 align:middle line:84%
And I think that a lot of
people live a fear-based life

00:03:24.960 --> 00:03:26.790 align:middle line:90%
even if they don't realize it.

00:03:26.790 --> 00:03:28.380 align:middle line:84%
Because that's
how it was for me.

00:03:28.380 --> 00:03:31.410 align:middle line:84%
I didn't realize I was
living a fear-based life.

00:03:31.410 --> 00:03:37.290 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of like when an
air conditioner goes off,

00:03:37.290 --> 00:03:39.000 align:middle line:90%
and you notice the silence.

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:41.680 align:middle line:84%
And you never knew it was
on in the first place.

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:42.900 align:middle line:90%
You couldn't hear it.

00:03:42.900 --> 00:03:46.207 align:middle line:84%
And only when it goes off,
you realized that it was on.

00:03:46.207 --> 00:03:47.040 align:middle line:90%
It's the same thing.

00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:51.480 align:middle line:84%
When the fear was gone, when
I was in that near-death space

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:54.720 align:middle line:84%
or in that death space,
and the fear was gone

00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:57.540 align:middle line:84%
did I realize that I had
been living my whole life

00:03:57.540 --> 00:03:59.550 align:middle line:90%
from a place of fear.

00:03:59.550 --> 00:04:01.883 align:middle line:84%
>> So interesting, we can
see it in other people.

00:04:01.883 --> 00:04:03.300 align:middle line:84%
We can say, oh,
they're fear based

00:04:03.300 --> 00:04:06.330 align:middle line:84%
or that's the worst case
scenario or something.

00:04:06.330 --> 00:04:08.820 align:middle line:84%
But we can not see
it in ourselves.

00:04:08.820 --> 00:04:12.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, because it's very--

00:04:12.330 --> 00:04:13.860 align:middle line:90%
I guess, it's very--

00:04:13.860 --> 00:04:17.050 align:middle line:90%
it's subtle or it's pervasive.

00:04:17.050 --> 00:04:18.750 align:middle line:90%
It's part of our culture.

00:04:18.750 --> 00:04:21.060 align:middle line:84%
For example, I grew up
in the Hindu culture.

00:04:21.060 --> 00:04:22.830 align:middle line:90%
My parents are Indian.

00:04:22.830 --> 00:04:27.390 align:middle line:84%
And I was-- a big
pressure on me as I

00:04:27.390 --> 00:04:30.000 align:middle line:84%
was growing up is that
you have to get married,

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.190 align:middle line:84%
and you have to have
an arranged marriage.

00:04:32.190 --> 00:04:37.080 align:middle line:84%
And in my culture, women
are not as valued as men.

00:04:37.080 --> 00:04:41.910 align:middle line:84%
In fact, a woman's
worth is measured

00:04:41.910 --> 00:04:45.330 align:middle line:84%
by how good they
are at housework

00:04:45.330 --> 00:04:48.300 align:middle line:84%
or how good they
are at serving men

00:04:48.300 --> 00:04:51.690 align:middle line:84%
or how valuable they are
to the men in their lives.

00:04:51.690 --> 00:04:53.670 align:middle line:90%
That's how your you're measured.

00:04:53.670 --> 00:04:55.890 align:middle line:84%
That's how you're
more worthy if you're

00:04:55.890 --> 00:04:57.910 align:middle line:84%
more valuable to the
men in your life.

00:04:57.910 --> 00:05:01.670 align:middle line:84%
So if you get older and
you're still single,

00:05:01.670 --> 00:05:03.960 align:middle line:90%
your value goes down.

00:05:03.960 --> 00:05:06.060 align:middle line:84%
A woman's more valuable
if she's married.

00:05:06.060 --> 00:05:08.850 align:middle line:84%
And the more important
the man she's married to,

00:05:08.850 --> 00:05:10.617 align:middle line:90%
the more important she is.

00:05:10.617 --> 00:05:12.450 align:middle line:84%
>> But that never made
sense to you, did it?

00:05:12.450 --> 00:05:13.290 align:middle line:90%
>> No, it didn't.

00:05:13.290 --> 00:05:15.310 align:middle line:84%
>> Even though you were
raised in that environment,

00:05:15.310 --> 00:05:16.810 align:middle line:84%
it just didn't work
for you, did it?

00:05:16.810 --> 00:05:20.940 align:middle line:84%
>> It didn't because what I
couldn't understand is how come

00:05:20.940 --> 00:05:24.840 align:middle line:84%
I'm being told that I can't
have higher education because it

00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:28.310 align:middle line:84%
will make me too smart and
less desirable for marriage.

00:05:28.310 --> 00:05:31.170 align:middle line:84%
And I have to learn to be a
subservient housewife and so

00:05:31.170 --> 00:05:31.970 align:middle line:90%
on.

00:05:31.970 --> 00:05:36.800 align:middle line:84%
But how come deep down
I have this yearning

00:05:36.800 --> 00:05:40.190 align:middle line:84%
to travel the world and
to earn my own money

00:05:40.190 --> 00:05:42.170 align:middle line:90%
and to be independent.

00:05:42.170 --> 00:05:45.230 align:middle line:84%
And there was kind
of discrepancy.

00:05:45.230 --> 00:05:49.190 align:middle line:84%
It's like if this yearning is
coming from inside me, surely,

00:05:49.190 --> 00:05:51.110 align:middle line:90%
I was made this way.

00:05:51.110 --> 00:05:54.140 align:middle line:84%
And I remember
getting into trouble

00:05:54.140 --> 00:05:59.570 align:middle line:84%
one time when we were at a
temple, where men and women had

00:05:59.570 --> 00:06:00.840 align:middle line:90%
to be separated.

00:06:00.840 --> 00:06:04.970 align:middle line:84%
But women had this tiny section,
and they were really cramped.

00:06:04.970 --> 00:06:08.330 align:middle line:84%
And men were sprawled
out in this big section.

00:06:08.330 --> 00:06:09.710 align:middle line:90%
And I just kind--

00:06:09.710 --> 00:06:10.620 align:middle line:90%
I was really young.

00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:13.520 align:middle line:84%
I said, oh, I want to go
hang in the bigger space.

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:15.270 align:middle line:84%
And my parents said,
you can't do that.

00:06:15.270 --> 00:06:16.070 align:middle line:90%
You're a girl.

00:06:16.070 --> 00:06:17.600 align:middle line:90%
You have to go there.

00:06:17.600 --> 00:06:19.850 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well,
then how can this

00:06:19.850 --> 00:06:23.390 align:middle line:84%
be called a place of
God, a place of worship

00:06:23.390 --> 00:06:24.710 align:middle line:90%
if there's inequality.

00:06:24.710 --> 00:06:28.670 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe that God
made the two genders unequal.

00:06:28.670 --> 00:06:31.350 align:middle line:84%
And I actually got in big
trouble for saying that.

00:06:31.350 --> 00:06:34.790 align:middle line:84%
I was told to go and apologize
in front of the deities

00:06:34.790 --> 00:06:36.360 align:middle line:90%
for being so disrespectful.

00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:37.160 align:middle line:90%
>> By your parents?

00:06:37.160 --> 00:06:38.360 align:middle line:90%
>> By my parents--

00:06:38.360 --> 00:06:40.620 align:middle line:84%
and yet, in my head,
it was like, no,

00:06:40.620 --> 00:06:43.230 align:middle line:84%
but the God I believe
in wouldn't do that.

00:06:43.230 --> 00:06:46.040 align:middle line:10%
>> So there was no influence
around you that was showing you

00:06:46.040 --> 00:06:46.910 align:middle line:10%
another way?

00:06:46.910 --> 00:06:53.020 align:middle line:84%
>> Not-- well, to an extent,
I grew up in a multicultural

00:06:53.020 --> 00:06:53.820 align:middle line:90%
society.

00:06:53.820 --> 00:06:56.570 align:middle line:84%
So from that perspective,
a lot of things

00:06:56.570 --> 00:06:57.900 align:middle line:90%
didn't make sense to me.

00:06:57.900 --> 00:07:01.250 align:middle line:84%
I never fit in because
I was going to school

00:07:01.250 --> 00:07:03.590 align:middle line:84%
in Hong Kong, which
is predominantly

00:07:03.590 --> 00:07:05.240 align:middle line:90%
a Chinese society.

00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:06.500 align:middle line:90%
But I was in a British--

00:07:06.500 --> 00:07:08.960 align:middle line:90%
an international school.

00:07:08.960 --> 00:07:11.900 align:middle line:84%
And in the school, there
were mostly British kids.

00:07:11.900 --> 00:07:14.270 align:middle line:84%
And my parents were
Indian, Hindus,

00:07:14.270 --> 00:07:16.970 align:middle line:84%
and I was expected to go
to the temple every week.

00:07:16.970 --> 00:07:19.280 align:middle line:90%
So I felt I didn't fit anywhere.

00:07:19.280 --> 00:07:21.770 align:middle line:84%
>> I bet you saw so many
different perspectives.

00:07:21.770 --> 00:07:24.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, and I had to make
sense of all these different

00:07:24.680 --> 00:07:26.150 align:middle line:90%
perspectives.

00:07:26.150 --> 00:07:28.940 align:middle line:84%
>> And so it makes sense that
you would have questioned

00:07:28.940 --> 00:07:30.950 align:middle line:90%
reality at the time.

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:33.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, so I was
questioning reality a lot.

00:07:33.980 --> 00:07:39.900 align:middle line:84%
But in my culture, I was being
judged as being rebellious.

00:07:39.900 --> 00:07:42.065 align:middle line:90%
But it genuinely--

00:07:42.065 --> 00:07:43.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Not curious, rebellious.

00:07:43.190 --> 00:07:43.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Not curious.

00:07:43.680 --> 00:07:44.960 align:middle line:84%
>> And so it was
not a good thing.

00:07:44.960 --> 00:07:46.170 align:middle line:90%
>> It was not a good thing.

00:07:46.170 --> 00:07:48.680 align:middle line:84%
>> So when you had
this death experience,

00:07:48.680 --> 00:07:51.740 align:middle line:84%
you didn't go to the tunnel or
see the light or anything like

00:07:51.740 --> 00:07:52.550 align:middle line:90%
that, right?

00:07:52.550 --> 00:07:54.110 align:middle line:90%
>> No, it was very different.

00:07:54.110 --> 00:07:58.430 align:middle line:84%
And I was told by people who
study near-death experiences

00:07:58.430 --> 00:08:02.870 align:middle line:84%
that it was probably because
it wasn't a sudden death.

00:08:02.870 --> 00:08:06.530 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't a car crash
or a heart attack

00:08:06.530 --> 00:08:08.960 align:middle line:84%
and that's probably
why I didn't go

00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:12.470 align:middle line:84%
like swooshing out through the
tunnel and towards the light.

00:08:12.470 --> 00:08:14.420 align:middle line:84%
Because it was a
gradual death, it

00:08:14.420 --> 00:08:17.880 align:middle line:84%
was like I had just slowly
come out of my body.

00:08:17.880 --> 00:08:20.360 align:middle line:10%
But what was really
interesting--

00:08:20.360 --> 00:08:23.130 align:middle line:10%
I just want to add here--
when I was growing up,

00:08:23.130 --> 00:08:27.170 align:middle line:10%
my dad and I clashed
a lot because he

00:08:27.170 --> 00:08:28.790 align:middle line:10%
thought I was too rebellious.

00:08:28.790 --> 00:08:33.799 align:middle line:84%
And, also, because I
ended up eventually

00:08:33.799 --> 00:08:35.630 align:middle line:84%
agreeing to an
arranged marriage.

00:08:35.630 --> 00:08:38.929 align:middle line:84%
And then three days before,
running away from it,

00:08:38.929 --> 00:08:42.960 align:middle line:84%
which brought a lot
of shame to my family,

00:08:42.960 --> 00:08:46.400 align:middle line:90%
to my then fiance's family.

00:08:46.400 --> 00:08:48.530 align:middle line:84%
So I was ostracized
from the community.

00:08:48.530 --> 00:08:52.340 align:middle line:84%
And my parents were told
that no man from my culture

00:08:52.340 --> 00:08:54.890 align:middle line:84%
would ever marry me
after what I'd done.

00:08:54.890 --> 00:08:57.830 align:middle line:84%
So I brought all
this shame to them.

00:08:57.830 --> 00:09:00.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Did you move
away at that time?

00:09:00.980 --> 00:09:05.130 align:middle line:84%
>> So I didn't
physically move away.

00:09:05.130 --> 00:09:08.120 align:middle line:84%
So I still had all
these people around me.

00:09:08.120 --> 00:09:10.730 align:middle line:84%
I had to deal with
all this shame.

00:09:10.730 --> 00:09:13.910 align:middle line:84%
And I do believe
that a lot of this

00:09:13.910 --> 00:09:15.780 align:middle line:90%
fear of not being good enough--

00:09:15.780 --> 00:09:17.630 align:middle line:84%
and this is what I
mean by all the fears--

00:09:17.630 --> 00:09:21.950 align:middle line:84%
fear of displeasing people,
fear of trying to meet

00:09:21.950 --> 00:09:23.690 align:middle line:90%
other people's expectations.

00:09:23.690 --> 00:09:26.630 align:middle line:84%
All of this contributes
to draining you.

00:09:26.630 --> 00:09:28.310 align:middle line:90%
It drains your energy.

00:09:28.310 --> 00:09:31.670 align:middle line:84%
And this is what eventually
contributed to my illness.

00:09:31.670 --> 00:09:36.590 align:middle line:84%
And then my best friend, I
watched her go through cancer.

00:09:36.590 --> 00:09:39.650 align:middle line:84%
I felt guilt that I was
healthy, and she was--

00:09:39.650 --> 00:09:41.940 align:middle line:90%
she had cancer.

00:09:41.940 --> 00:09:45.740 align:middle line:84%
So it's this fear again
of not being good enough

00:09:45.740 --> 00:09:48.530 align:middle line:84%
for my friend, feeling
guilty if something good is

00:09:48.530 --> 00:09:49.940 align:middle line:90%
happening with me.

00:09:49.940 --> 00:09:54.360 align:middle line:84%
And then I started to develop
a fear of getting cancer.

00:09:54.360 --> 00:09:58.220 align:middle line:84%
And so I started to eat
really healthy, interestingly,

00:09:58.220 --> 00:10:03.110 align:middle line:84%
but out of a fear of disease not
from a place of loving my life

00:10:03.110 --> 00:10:04.700 align:middle line:90%
and wanting to live life--

00:10:04.700 --> 00:10:06.530 align:middle line:90%
live a long and healthy life.

00:10:06.530 --> 00:10:11.330 align:middle line:84%
It was out of fear of illness
that I would eat organic,

00:10:11.330 --> 00:10:14.750 align:middle line:84%
and I would make my
own wheatgrass shots,

00:10:14.750 --> 00:10:18.290 align:middle line:84%
and I would source
all these supplements.

00:10:18.290 --> 00:10:21.270 align:middle line:84%
But all of it out of a
fear of getting cancer.

00:10:21.270 --> 00:10:23.752 align:middle line:84%
And then I got
diagnosed with cancer.

00:10:23.752 --> 00:10:25.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, when you were in
that death experience,

00:10:25.710 --> 00:10:28.110 align:middle line:84%
you wrote about
seeing your father.

00:10:28.110 --> 00:10:29.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:10:29.340 --> 00:10:32.655 align:middle line:90%
>> And having him forgive you.

00:10:32.655 --> 00:10:34.530 align:middle line:84%
love-- I mean, this is
called love, isn't it?

00:10:34.530 --> 00:10:38.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, so what happened is
when I was on the other side.

00:10:38.380 --> 00:10:40.110 align:middle line:90%
And I saw my dad.

00:10:40.110 --> 00:10:45.090 align:middle line:84%
And I thought that I would
experience a lot of judgment,

00:10:45.090 --> 00:10:48.690 align:middle line:84%
having lived this
lifetime of thinking

00:10:48.690 --> 00:10:51.780 align:middle line:84%
that I had got everything wrong,
that I was rebellious, that I'd

00:10:51.780 --> 00:10:52.920 align:middle line:90%
run away from a marriage.

00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:54.600 align:middle line:90%
And I'd screwed up so much.

00:10:54.600 --> 00:10:57.030 align:middle line:90%
And I put my parents to shame.

00:10:57.030 --> 00:11:00.690 align:middle line:84%
And so here I was
face-to-face with my dad.

00:11:00.690 --> 00:11:05.760 align:middle line:84%
And all I experienced from him
was pure, unconditional love.

00:11:05.760 --> 00:11:08.460 align:middle line:84%
That was all that was
emanating from him.

00:11:08.460 --> 00:11:10.320 align:middle line:90%
It was like he understood me.

00:11:10.320 --> 00:11:12.810 align:middle line:90%
He understood everything.

00:11:12.810 --> 00:11:14.970 align:middle line:90%
It was like I was transparent.

00:11:14.970 --> 00:11:17.280 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even have
to use language.

00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:21.600 align:middle line:84%
We were communicating
just purely energetically.

00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:24.360 align:middle line:84%
And so there was no room
for miscommunication.

00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:27.450 align:middle line:84%
And it was like I
was transparent.

00:11:27.450 --> 00:11:31.380 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I realized
that when we crossover,

00:11:31.380 --> 00:11:34.780 align:middle line:84%
we don't just leave
behind our bodies.

00:11:34.780 --> 00:11:41.040 align:middle line:84%
We also leave behind our
gender, our culture, our beliefs

00:11:41.040 --> 00:11:45.810 align:middle line:84%
and all these layers that we
accumulate over this lifetime.

00:11:45.810 --> 00:11:47.735 align:middle line:84%
>> Was your father
crossed over at that time?

00:11:47.735 --> 00:11:49.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, he was.

00:11:49.230 --> 00:11:52.920 align:middle line:84%
My father had died
10 years prior.

00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:53.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:11:53.970 --> 00:11:59.650 align:middle line:84%
>> And so there he had been
trying to arrange a marriage

00:11:59.650 --> 00:12:00.450 align:middle line:90%
for me.

00:12:00.450 --> 00:12:03.790 align:middle line:84%
But at the time he died,
I wasn't even married yet.

00:12:03.790 --> 00:12:06.690 align:middle line:84%
>> And so it was
unresolved in you.

00:12:06.690 --> 00:12:08.440 align:middle line:90%
There's another layer of guilt.

00:12:08.440 --> 00:12:12.360 align:middle line:84%
>> There was another layer
of guilt that I'd never gone

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:13.560 align:middle line:90%
through a marriage.

00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:17.170 align:middle line:84%
And it was my father's
dream to see me married.

00:12:17.170 --> 00:12:23.220 align:middle line:84%
>> So this transformed you so
much when you came back in, how

00:12:23.220 --> 00:12:28.560 align:middle line:84%
did the tumors shrink and the
cancer go away in three weeks?

00:12:28.560 --> 00:12:30.600 align:middle line:90%
>> The cancer just disappeared.

00:12:30.600 --> 00:12:34.920 align:middle line:84%
And I just want to say
that before I came back

00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:36.150 align:middle line:90%
into my body--

00:12:36.150 --> 00:12:38.220 align:middle line:90%
and I was given the choice--

00:12:38.220 --> 00:12:40.540 align:middle line:84%
but my dad said,
it's not your time.

00:12:40.540 --> 00:12:43.680 align:middle line:84%
And you must go back in
live your life fearlessly.

00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:47.220 align:middle line:84%
In that moment, I actually
understood that what he meant

00:12:47.220 --> 00:12:50.280 align:middle line:84%
was go back and be
yourself fearlessly.

00:12:50.280 --> 00:12:54.360 align:middle line:84%
It was like he was gifting
me something that he

00:12:54.360 --> 00:12:57.180 align:middle line:90%
felt he had taken away from me.

00:12:57.180 --> 00:13:00.960 align:middle line:84%
Because I felt that
he felt responsible

00:13:00.960 --> 00:13:03.960 align:middle line:90%
for me growing up so fearfully.

00:13:03.960 --> 00:13:08.810 align:middle line:84%
And so he was gifting me
a second lease of life.

00:13:08.810 --> 00:13:13.200 align:middle line:84%
And his message was go back
and live your life fearlessly.

00:13:13.200 --> 00:13:17.410 align:middle line:84%
And so when I came back, I
knew that the cancer wasn't

00:13:17.410 --> 00:13:18.910 align:middle line:84%
going to heal, and
that it was going

00:13:18.910 --> 00:13:20.610 align:middle line:90%
to heal very, very quickly.

00:13:20.610 --> 00:13:25.350 align:middle line:84%
Because I now understood that
it was an accumulation of all

00:13:25.350 --> 00:13:29.610 align:middle line:84%
these years of beating myself
up and judging myself and living

00:13:29.610 --> 00:13:30.820 align:middle line:90%
in fear.

00:13:30.820 --> 00:13:33.630 align:middle line:84%
And it was just an
accumulation of all this

00:13:33.630 --> 00:13:35.820 align:middle line:84%
over all these years
that had drained me

00:13:35.820 --> 00:13:38.100 align:middle line:90%
to the point of getting cancer.

00:13:38.100 --> 00:13:40.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you wrote about
it in "Dying to be Me."

00:13:40.830 --> 00:13:43.200 align:middle line:10%
And I wouldn't
know-- when you have

00:13:43.200 --> 00:13:49.860 align:middle line:10%
other women from your
culture, what did they respond

00:13:49.860 --> 00:13:51.660 align:middle line:10%
when you wrote this book?

00:13:51.660 --> 00:13:53.730 align:middle line:84%
>> They responded
really favorably.

00:13:53.730 --> 00:13:55.530 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't expect that.

00:13:55.530 --> 00:13:56.980 align:middle line:90%
I really didn't expect that.

00:13:56.980 --> 00:14:00.750 align:middle line:84%
And when the publishers
told me that they were

00:14:00.750 --> 00:14:04.230 align:middle line:90%
going to also publish in India.

00:14:04.230 --> 00:14:05.940 align:middle line:84%
And they said Hay
House India was

00:14:05.940 --> 00:14:08.580 align:middle line:84%
going to publish and
promote it in India,

00:14:08.580 --> 00:14:10.930 align:middle line:84%
I was actually a
little bit concerned.

00:14:10.930 --> 00:14:12.480 align:middle line:84%
I thought, oh,
Indian people are not

00:14:12.480 --> 00:14:17.050 align:middle line:84%
going to want to hear what
I've written in the book.

00:14:17.050 --> 00:14:18.690 align:middle line:84%
>> You're living
your life fearlessly.

00:14:18.690 --> 00:14:22.290 align:middle line:84%
>> But I thought, OK, I'm living
my life fearlessly-- exactly.

00:14:22.290 --> 00:14:24.660 align:middle line:90%
I have to just go with the flow.

00:14:24.660 --> 00:14:27.500 align:middle line:84%
And you won't believe it,
the book hit number one

00:14:27.500 --> 00:14:28.490 align:middle line:90%
>> In India?

00:14:28.490 --> 00:14:29.010 align:middle line:90%
>> In India.

00:14:29.010 --> 00:14:29.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:14:29.810 --> 00:14:31.650 align:middle line:84%
>> I actually get
recognized on the streets.

00:14:31.650 --> 00:14:32.720 align:middle line:90%
I could not believe.

00:14:32.720 --> 00:14:34.020 align:middle line:90%
>> That says something.

00:14:34.020 --> 00:14:37.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, and that surprised
me very pleasantly in a very

00:14:37.690 --> 00:14:38.490 align:middle line:90%
pleasant way.

00:14:38.490 --> 00:14:41.380 align:middle line:84%
It was like the women
were ready to hear it.

00:14:41.380 --> 00:14:42.900 align:middle line:90%
They were so open.

00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:44.730 align:middle line:90%
They have been amazing.

00:14:44.730 --> 00:14:46.920 align:middle line:84%
The Indian culture,
the Indian women--

00:14:46.920 --> 00:14:48.000 align:middle line:90%
they've been amazing.

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:49.760 align:middle line:90%
>> What have they said?

00:14:49.760 --> 00:14:53.460 align:middle line:84%
>> They have said I was really
brave, not just to do that,

00:14:53.460 --> 00:14:55.950 align:middle line:84%
but they also feel I'm
brave to share that,

00:14:55.950 --> 00:14:59.940 align:middle line:84%
to share that I did that and
to share with other women that

00:14:59.940 --> 00:15:01.890 align:middle line:90%
they have to be themselves.

00:15:01.890 --> 00:15:03.780 align:middle line:84%
Because some of the
things I say in the book

00:15:03.780 --> 00:15:07.380 align:middle line:84%
was how I was
measured by my ability

00:15:07.380 --> 00:15:11.280 align:middle line:84%
to do housework and things like
that, which women relate to,

00:15:11.280 --> 00:15:13.437 align:middle line:90%
especially in Asian cultures.

00:15:13.437 --> 00:15:14.520 align:middle line:90%
>> And you wrote about it.

00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:17.200 align:middle line:84%
>> And I wrote about it,
and I speak about it.

00:15:17.200 --> 00:15:21.180 align:middle line:84%
And so they actually--
it gives them permission

00:15:21.180 --> 00:15:26.320 align:middle line:84%
to speak about it or it gives
them permission to stand up

00:15:26.320 --> 00:15:29.560 align:middle line:84%
and say, look, I'm not going
to be measured this way.

00:15:29.560 --> 00:15:33.560 align:middle line:84%
>> And those that want to hold
on to the tradition, it's fine.

00:15:33.560 --> 00:15:34.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:15:34.360 --> 00:15:36.020 align:middle line:84%
>> And those that
see a different way,

00:15:36.020 --> 00:15:39.530 align:middle line:84%
you kind of gave them a little
bit of permission to speak

00:15:39.530 --> 00:15:40.330 align:middle line:90%
about it.

00:15:40.330 --> 00:15:44.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, and, again, there's
nothing wrong with being

00:15:44.080 --> 00:15:46.360 align:middle line:90%
a homemaker, nothing at all.

00:15:46.360 --> 00:15:48.200 align:middle line:90%
And that's not what I'm saying.

00:15:48.200 --> 00:15:51.490 align:middle line:84%
But I think everybody should be
free to do what comes naturally

00:15:51.490 --> 00:15:52.300 align:middle line:90%
to them.

00:15:52.300 --> 00:15:54.610 align:middle line:84%
>> And your message is
more about the self-love.

00:15:54.610 --> 00:15:56.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, exactly.

00:15:56.530 --> 00:15:59.620 align:middle line:84%
You have to love yourself
enough to give yourself

00:15:59.620 --> 00:16:02.240 align:middle line:90%
permission to be who you are.

00:16:02.240 --> 00:16:06.140 align:middle line:84%
You see one of the problems is
when you don't love yourself,

00:16:06.140 --> 00:16:09.490 align:middle line:84%
you assume that if you don't
toe the line, if you don't

00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:12.010 align:middle line:84%
do what society
expects you to do,

00:16:12.010 --> 00:16:15.200 align:middle line:84%
you assume it's going to
make you a bad person.

00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:18.010 align:middle line:84%
But when you love yourself,
you realize, no, what

00:16:18.010 --> 00:16:20.830 align:middle line:84%
I have to offer is
actually something better

00:16:20.830 --> 00:16:22.870 align:middle line:84%
than what they're
asking me to do.

00:16:22.870 --> 00:16:27.520 align:middle line:84%
And their expectation is
actually suppressing me,

00:16:27.520 --> 00:16:30.040 align:middle line:84%
but I want to show
them who I really am.

00:16:30.040 --> 00:16:32.830 align:middle line:90%
That's what self-love is.

00:16:32.830 --> 00:16:36.370 align:middle line:84%
>> So in your experience, what
do you think made you such

00:16:36.370 --> 00:16:37.900 align:middle line:90%
a people pleaser?

00:16:37.900 --> 00:16:42.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, when I was growing
up, my parents were Indian as I

00:16:42.440 --> 00:16:43.240 align:middle line:90%
mentioned.

00:16:43.240 --> 00:16:46.420 align:middle line:84%
And I grew up in Hong Kong,
which is predominantly

00:16:46.420 --> 00:16:48.310 align:middle line:90%
a Chinese society.

00:16:48.310 --> 00:16:50.330 align:middle line:84%
Well, my parents were
trying to hold on

00:16:50.330 --> 00:16:53.770 align:middle line:84%
to our Hindu cultural values,
and I went to a school

00:16:53.770 --> 00:16:55.480 align:middle line:90%
with British kids.

00:16:55.480 --> 00:17:00.580 align:middle line:84%
And what I felt was that
I didn't belong anywhere.

00:17:00.580 --> 00:17:02.710 align:middle line:90%
I was like a cultural hybrid.

00:17:02.710 --> 00:17:06.130 align:middle line:84%
These British kids all
were together in a clique.

00:17:06.130 --> 00:17:07.869 align:middle line:84%
The Chinese kids
in my neighborhood

00:17:07.869 --> 00:17:09.800 align:middle line:90%
were together in a clique.

00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And when I would go
with the Indian kids,

00:17:12.130 --> 00:17:14.200 align:middle line:90%
I didn't even feel very Indian.

00:17:14.200 --> 00:17:17.859 align:middle line:84%
Because I was so exposed to
the British kids at school

00:17:17.859 --> 00:17:19.660 align:middle line:90%
that I was westernized.

00:17:19.660 --> 00:17:22.690 align:middle line:84%
I was a westernized
version of an Indian kid.

00:17:22.690 --> 00:17:26.290 align:middle line:84%
Because I didn't want to do the
whole arranged marriage thing.

00:17:26.290 --> 00:17:27.609 align:middle line:90%
And I was very different.

00:17:27.609 --> 00:17:30.830 align:middle line:84%
So I felt I didn't
belong anywhere.

00:17:30.830 --> 00:17:33.340 align:middle line:84%
And, yet, I had this
longing that I really

00:17:33.340 --> 00:17:35.050 align:middle line:90%
wanted to belong somewhere.

00:17:35.050 --> 00:17:37.780 align:middle line:84%
So I found myself
bending over backwards

00:17:37.780 --> 00:17:41.170 align:middle line:84%
with every cultural
group that I would become

00:17:41.170 --> 00:17:43.100 align:middle line:90%
who they wanted me to be.

00:17:43.100 --> 00:17:45.460 align:middle line:84%
So I was literally
a people pleaser.

00:17:45.460 --> 00:17:47.590 align:middle line:84%
I would become who
they wanted me to be so

00:17:47.590 --> 00:17:51.370 align:middle line:84%
that I could belong to a clique,
so that I could be accepted.

00:17:51.370 --> 00:17:55.807 align:middle line:84%
And for me that was the biggest
thing-- wanting to belong.

00:17:55.807 --> 00:17:58.390 align:middle line:84%
>> What about the opposite-- if
someone doesn't feel like they

00:17:58.390 --> 00:18:00.190 align:middle line:90%
belong, and they become a bully.

00:18:00.190 --> 00:18:03.910 align:middle line:90%
And they ostracized themselves.

00:18:03.910 --> 00:18:07.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, usually, I think even
bullies it comes from a place

00:18:07.330 --> 00:18:10.853 align:middle line:84%
of not belonging and
wanting to belong.

00:18:10.853 --> 00:18:12.520 align:middle line:84%
It's like a desire
of wanting to belong.

00:18:12.520 --> 00:18:15.380 align:middle line:84%
I was bullied because
I didn't belong.

00:18:15.380 --> 00:18:16.670 align:middle line:90%
I was the outsider.

00:18:16.670 --> 00:18:21.910 align:middle line:84%
I was the brown face amongst
a whole bunch of white faces.

00:18:21.910 --> 00:18:23.830 align:middle line:90%
So I was the one picked on.

00:18:23.830 --> 00:18:25.540 align:middle line:84%
And that used to
really pained me

00:18:25.540 --> 00:18:28.070 align:middle line:84%
that I didn't feel
I belonged anywhere.

00:18:28.070 --> 00:18:31.000 align:middle line:84%
But when I had the
near-death experience,

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:34.780 align:middle line:84%
I understood why I
was the way I was.

00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:39.790 align:middle line:84%
I understood why that I
had spent this lifetime

00:18:39.790 --> 00:18:42.160 align:middle line:90%
of being this unique person.

00:18:42.160 --> 00:18:45.340 align:middle line:84%
Because it turned out
that that was my gift.

00:18:45.340 --> 00:18:50.590 align:middle line:84%
Because today I am so glad
that I don't belong anywhere

00:18:50.590 --> 00:18:53.470 align:middle line:84%
because it feels like
I belong everywhere.

00:18:53.470 --> 00:18:56.080 align:middle line:84%
>> And you have so many
different perspectives to share

00:18:56.080 --> 00:18:59.110 align:middle line:84%
and understanding
and compassion.

00:18:59.110 --> 00:19:02.510 align:middle line:84%
So belonging turned
to your greatest gift.

00:19:02.510 --> 00:19:05.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes and, in fact, not
actually ending up belonging

00:19:05.620 --> 00:19:10.330 align:middle line:84%
anywhere turned into my greatest
gift because I actually am able

00:19:10.330 --> 00:19:16.510 align:middle line:84%
to see how all the cultures
offer a different facet of what

00:19:16.510 --> 00:19:18.700 align:middle line:90%
makes up this universe.

00:19:18.700 --> 00:19:20.950 align:middle line:90%
I feel I belong to all of them.

00:19:20.950 --> 00:19:22.300 align:middle line:90%
>> That's beautiful.

00:19:22.300 --> 00:19:25.540 align:middle line:84%
So for people who have not
had this experience of cancer

00:19:25.540 --> 00:19:27.310 align:middle line:84%
and going through
all that you did,

00:19:27.310 --> 00:19:31.750 align:middle line:84%
how do you teach them to
have that level of self love

00:19:31.750 --> 00:19:36.070 align:middle line:84%
without going through
such an awakening?

00:19:36.070 --> 00:19:40.270 align:middle line:84%
>> So there are actually
many things I tell people.

00:19:40.270 --> 00:19:44.380 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people believe
that self love means being

00:19:44.380 --> 00:19:46.840 align:middle line:90%
egotistical or narcissistic.

00:19:46.840 --> 00:19:48.560 align:middle line:90%
In fact, it's the opposite.

00:19:48.560 --> 00:19:51.370 align:middle line:84%
People who are egotistical
and narcissistic

00:19:51.370 --> 00:19:52.610 align:middle line:90%
don't love themselves.

00:19:52.610 --> 00:19:54.550 align:middle line:90%
And so they're overcompensating.

00:19:54.550 --> 00:19:57.040 align:middle line:84%
When someone truly
loves themselves

00:19:57.040 --> 00:20:00.460 align:middle line:84%
they're very comfortable
even sitting back in a corner

00:20:00.460 --> 00:20:04.570 align:middle line:84%
and not being heard because
you know who you are,

00:20:04.570 --> 00:20:06.460 align:middle line:90%
you know what you stand for.

00:20:06.460 --> 00:20:10.490 align:middle line:84%
You're very happy even to
let other people shine.

00:20:10.490 --> 00:20:13.330 align:middle line:84%
>> And so the way
that I tell people--

00:20:13.330 --> 00:20:17.770 align:middle line:84%
or the way that I suggest to
people to ask yourself whether

00:20:17.770 --> 00:20:19.300 align:middle line:90%
you love yourself or not.

00:20:19.300 --> 00:20:20.870 align:middle line:90%
There's a couple of things.

00:20:20.870 --> 00:20:25.300 align:middle line:84%
One is how good are
you at receiving.

00:20:25.300 --> 00:20:27.130 align:middle line:90%
And this is a telltale sign.

00:20:27.130 --> 00:20:32.650 align:middle line:84%
People who don't love
themselves, who are--

00:20:32.650 --> 00:20:37.150 align:middle line:84%
people who are particularly
sensitive and empathetic

00:20:37.150 --> 00:20:39.100 align:middle line:84%
and don't love
themselves, they're

00:20:39.100 --> 00:20:40.990 align:middle line:90%
very, very good at giving.

00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:43.550 align:middle line:84%
Because they become
people pleasers.

00:20:43.550 --> 00:20:44.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Over giving.

00:20:44.350 --> 00:20:45.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Over giving.

00:20:45.190 --> 00:20:47.360 align:middle line:84%
>> So that means if
you're sensitive.

00:20:47.360 --> 00:20:50.860 align:middle line:84%
And if you are not able
to express that self love,

00:20:50.860 --> 00:20:53.770 align:middle line:84%
