00:53:10.240 --> 00:53:13.300 align:middle line:84%
Because it is, again,
about taking your power

00:53:13.300 --> 00:53:16.090 align:middle line:84%
back that you have
that connection.

00:53:16.090 --> 00:53:20.110 align:middle line:84%
And I feel that is really
important because right now

00:53:20.110 --> 00:53:24.430 align:middle line:84%
what we do is we tend to
always go outside of us

00:53:24.430 --> 00:53:26.230 align:middle line:90%
to search for answers.

00:53:26.230 --> 00:53:30.640 align:middle line:84%
Now, the way I look at it is
what I get from the outside

00:53:30.640 --> 00:53:33.460 align:middle line:90%
is information not answers--

00:53:33.460 --> 00:53:35.020 align:middle line:90%
information.

00:53:35.020 --> 00:53:37.120 align:middle line:84%
And it's great to have
a lot of information

00:53:37.120 --> 00:53:42.640 align:middle line:84%
because it expands your library
from which to choose answers.

00:53:42.640 --> 00:53:48.250 align:middle line:84%
But all that information--
not all of it is right for you

00:53:48.250 --> 00:53:51.640 align:middle line:90%
at any particular given time.

00:53:51.640 --> 00:53:54.760 align:middle line:84%
Answers have to
come from within.

00:53:54.760 --> 00:53:56.490 align:middle line:84%
Information can
come from outside.

00:53:56.490 --> 00:53:58.823 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's OK, you just
have to be able to filter it.

00:53:58.823 --> 00:54:00.140 align:middle line:90%
It makes so much sense.

00:54:00.140 --> 00:54:04.340 align:middle line:84%
I have a new permission now
